Implementations of `DocumentJoiner` take a map of `Query` objects and their corresponding lists of `Document` lists as input. The `join` method returns a single list of `Document` objects representing the combined results. For example, using `ConcatenationDocumentJoiner`:

```java
Map<Query, List<List<Document>>> documentsForQuery = ...;
DocumentJoiner documentJoiner = new ConcatenationDocumentJoiner();
List<Document> documents = documentJoiner.join(documentsForQuery);
```

